    "question": "Forty eight hours after sustaining a blunt abdominal injury, a 15-year-old  boy presents with hematuria and pain in the left side of abdomen. On  examination, he has a pulse rate of 96/minute with a BP of 110/70 mm Hg.  His Hb is 10.8 g% with a PCV of 31%. The blood urea is 32 mg%. Abdominal  examination revealed tenderness in left lumbar region but no palpable mass.  The most appropriate investigation to diagnose and find the extent of renal  injury would be",
