    "answer": "a",
    "explanation": "Simple myopia is the most common type of myopia <br>which progresses during childhood and adolescence and seldom exceeds 5-<br>6D. It generally stops by the age of 21. Treatment of myopia: <br>• Concave spherical glass <br>• Contact lens—ideal substitute in high myopia <br>• Surgery—(i) radial keratotomy (RK)—for low degree myopia only (–2 to <br>–6 D), (ii) LASIK—for correcting myopia of –6 to –30 D, (iii) <br>photorefractive keratectomy—good result low degree (–2 to –6 D) <br>myopia, (iv) automated lamellar keratectomy (ALK) can correct myopia <br>of –6 to –32 D.",
