    "explanation": "Causes of chronic diarrhea: <br>1. Osmotic diarrhea—clues—stool volume decreases with fasting, <br>increased stool osmotic gap; (i) Medications—antacids, lactulose, <br>sorbitol, (ii) disaccharidase deficiency—lactose intolerance, (iii) <br>factitious diarrhea—magnesium (antacids, laxatives). <br>2. Secretory diarrhea—clues—large volume (>1 L/day), little change with <br>fasting, normal stool osmotic gap; (i) hormonally mediated—vipoma, <br>carcinoid, medullary carcinoma of thyroid (calcitonin), Zollinger-Ellison <br>syndrome (gastrin), (ii) factitious diarrhea (laxative abuse), <br>phenolphthalein, cascara, senna, (iii) villous adenoma, (iv) bile salt <br>malabsorption (ileal resection, Crohn's ileitis, postcholecystectomy, (v) <br>medications.",
