    "explanation": "Etiopathogenesis of nephritic syndrome—divided <br>into: <br>Idiopathic <br>Secondary <br>Infantile <br>• MCNS (75% <br>of children <br>and 15% of <br>adult) <br> • <br>FSGS (10% of <br>children, 15% <br>of adult) <br> <br>• MPGN (10%) <br>• Membranous nephropathy, (<5% <br>in children and 50% of adult) <br> • <br>Membranoproliferative GN, renal <br>vein thrombosis, malignant <br>hypertension, P. malariae infection, <br>syphilis, hepatitis B, infective <br>endocarditis, sickle-cell disease, <br>varicella, ventriculoatrial shunt <br>infection, AIDS <br> • Associated <br>systemic disease—SLE, PAN, <br>microscopic polyarteritis, <br>Wegener's granulomatosis, <br>amyloidosis, DM, HS purpura <br> <br>• Drugs—(a) membranous type—<br>penicillamine, captopril, gold, <br>NSAIDs, mercurials compound; (b) <br>minimal changes—probenecid, <br>ethosuximide, methimazole, Li; (c) <br>proliferative GN—procainamide, <br>chlorpropamide, phenytoin, <br>• Primary—(a) congenital <br>nephritic syndrome—<br>\"Finnish\" microcystic <br>disease, (b) diffuse <br>mesangial sclerosis, (c) <br>minimal change, (d) focal <br>segmental, (e) Drash <br>syndrome <br> • <br>Secondary—syphilis, CMV, <br>toxoplasmosis, mercury <br>and nail-patella syndrome <br>trimethadione, paramethadione <br><br> • Tumors—carcinoma, <br>Hodgkin's disease, chronic <br>lymphatic leukemia <br> • <br>Hereditary disease—Alport's <br>disease, Fabry's disease",
