    "explanation": "The International Commission on Radiological <br>Protection (ICRP) recommended that genetic dose to the whole population <br>from all sources additional to the natural background radiation should not <br>exceed 5 rem over a period of 30 years. • 1 becquerel (Bq) is equal to 1 <br>disintegration/second. 1 Bq = 27 picocurie. • Roentgen is the unit of exposure. <br>Amount of radiation exposed in air at a given point. 1 roentgen = 2.58 × 10⁴ <br>coulomb/kg. • Rad is the unit of absorbed dose, i.e., amount of radioactive <br>energy absorbed per gram of tissue. 1 rad = 0.01 Gy (gray). • Rem is the <br>product of absorbed dose and modifying factor, 100 rem = 1 Sv (Sievert).",
