    "question": "Consider the following statements:  Specific features suggestive of tricuspid regurgitation consist of:  1. Systolic pulsations of the liver  2. Diastolic thrill at left lower sternal border  3. Prominent V waves in jugular venous pulse  4. Deep S waves in V1 lead and tall R waves in V6 lead ECG Which of the  statements given above is/are correct?",
